OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBoohoo ad banned for       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fobjectifying and           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fsexualising women          
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A T-shirt advert for retailer Boohoo   
OL,6, has been banned after the Advertising  
OL,7, Standards Authority (ASA) ruled it     
OL,8, objectified and sexualised women.      
OL,10,FThe online fashion company's ad showed 
OL,11,Fa model wearing a T-shirt with         
OL,12,Fthong-style bikini bottoms and         
OL,13,Ftrainers.                              
OL,15,FBoohoo, which has been criticised for  
OL,16,Fits racy marketing before, said the    
OL,17,Fmodel was wearing the T-shirt with a   
OL,18,Fbikini as part of their swimwear range.
OL,20,FThe company said it was disappointed by
OL,21,Fthe ruling, but has removed the images.
